{{Beauty pageant | winner = [[Fay Lanphier]] | represented = {{flagicon|California}} [[Miss California]] | date = September 11, 1925 | presenters = King Neptune ([[Ernest Torrence]]) | entrants = 66 | placements = 15 | venue = [[Million Dollar Pier]] Ballroom, [[Atlantic City]], [[New Jersey]] | broadcaster = }}'''Miss America 1925''', the 5th [[Miss America]] pageant, was held at the [[Million Dollar Pier]] in [[Atlantic City, New Jersey]] on September 11, 1925. Entrants from the West Coast, Miss California (from Oakland) and Miss Los Angeles, captured the top two awards. The newly crowned beauty queen was a runner-up in the 1924 competition.<ref>{{cite news|title=Miss America's Smile Her Greatest Asset|date=1925-09-23|publisher=The Pittsburgh Press|page=6}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Miss America Is Fay Lanphier Of California|date=1925-09-12|publisher=Sandusky Star-Journal|page=11}}</ref>
Reports were received that King Neptune, portrayed by actor [[Ernest Torrence]], somehow fell into the ocean and had to be pulled out ("rescued") by lifeguards. Also on hand for the final night of pageant activities was Trition, son of Neptune, as played by [[Douglas Fairbanks, Jr.]]<ref>{{cite news|title=16 Entrants In Beauty Finals|last=Universal Service| date=1924-09-11|publisher=San Antonio Light|page=2}}</ref>
